The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Saturday, June 12, 2004  Good Morning Hello It's Saturday, June 12, 2004				 																Road to avoid				 																																	Gariahat to Ballygunge Phari. Dug up for tram track dereservation.				 																Party time				 																																	Chill out at The H2O Party and a fashion show at Hotel Hindustan International, 8 pm onwards.				 																																	Check out the tracks of 8PM Bermuda at the music album launch, followed by a Caribbean rain dance, at Spice Garden, on VIP Road, at 8.30 pm.				 																Soiree				 																																	Enjoy an evening of music, poetry-reading and story-telling, featuring Alokananda Roy, Parambrata Chatterjee, Renu Roy, Bani Basu, Bikram Ghosh and others at Tollygunge Club, 7 pm.				 																Discussion				 																																	Take part in an adda on Gao Xingjian and his works at Srijans rooftop, from 5 pm to 7 pm. 				 																Felicitation				 																																	Attend a function to felicitate Speaker Somnath Chatterjee at Great Eastern Hotel, at 5 pm. By invitation only.				 																Dance				 																																	Check out a recital, presented by Open Doors and Chandril Odissi Centre, Gyan Manch, 6.30 pm.				 																																	Learn the intricacies of kathak at a workshop at Moulali Yuva Kendra.				 																																	Take your kids to Mamata Shankars dance workshop at Nehru Childrens Museum, 3 pm to 4.30 pm.				 																Art beat				 																																	Spend time amid artworks at CIMA Gallery, from 2 pm to 7 pm.
